title: Voorhees' Kathryn Roncoroni is lehighvalleylive Field Hockey Player of the Week
text:
Senior Kathryn Roncoroni is having another big season for Voorhees' field hockey team (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 01, 2015 7:30 AM 
FIELD HOCKEY PLAYER OF THE WEEK Kathryn Roncoroni (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) 
Kathryn Roncoron i, Voorhees 
Roncoroni, a senior forward, registered five goals and three assists in the Vikings' 2-1 week. 
She racked up three goals and two assists in a 7-0 triumph over Somerville, scored her team's goal in a 2-1 overtime loss to Madison, and contributed a goal and an assist in a 2-0 win over Shore Regional. 
Roncoroni, an American University recruit, had 16 goals and 6 assists through eight games this season. 
Honorable mention :Sr. F Lauren Resh , Nazareth; Jr. M Cheyenne Ott , Bangor; Sr. M Dana Turner , Moravian Academy; Shae Banas , Freedom; Sr. F Quinn Bachman , Catasauqua; Sr. M Dana Evans , Pen Argyl; Jr. F Courtney Page , Northwestern; So. F Meghan Reese , Southern Lehigh; Jr. F Sophie Boyle , Southern Lehigh; Jr. F Dani Profita , Warren Hills; Jr. F Molly Gorczyca , Hackettstown.
